ree Kings, Insomnia, and the made-for-TV movie Brian's Song.  He was a graduate of the University of Virginia.", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-08-01T16:30:19.308258+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 4844, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paul_Junger_Witt"}], "uuid": "c9c0f410-5505-44a8-b00f-6efb284c9e84", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "26258", "external_references": [{"id": 25392, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q7151660"}, {"id": 30696, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "78385390"}, {"id": 30697, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "no97051234"}, {"id": 30698, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-no97051234"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-05T23:47:18.561793+10:00"}]}